While working on this project these were my Project Findings :


Virat Kohli's performance showed remarkable consistency during 2016–2019, making it one of the strongest phases of his international career.

Between 2020 and 2022, his form declined, with fewer centuries and comparatively lower run-scoring than in previous years.

From 2023 onwards, he regained his rhythm and returned to scoring consistently across major tournaments.

His first international century came in 2009, marking the beginning of an extraordinary batting journey.

His most recent international century reflects his ability to adapt and continue performing at the highest level.

ODI cricket has been his most successful format, contributing the highest share of his international runs and centuries.

The dashboard highlights his consistency through batting average, strike rate, centuries, and yearly run trends across all formats.

If Virat Kohli continues his current form, he has a strong chance of breaking records such as the most international centuries and climbing further among the highest run-scorers in international cricket.
